&lt;h2 id="Basics-of-Make-for-reproducible-research"&gt;Basics of &lt;code&gt;Make&lt;/code&gt; for reproducible research&lt;a class="anchor-link" href="#Basics-of-Make-for-reproducible-research"&gt;&amp;#182;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"&gt;&lt;div class="prompt input_prompt"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="inner_cell"&gt;
&lt;div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;A research project ca be seen as a tree of dependencies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the report depends on the figures and tables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the figurese and tables depend on the data and the analysis scripts used to process this data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make is a tool for creating output files from their dependencies through pre-specified rules&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>[Paper] Data Analysis with Latent Variable Models</title><link href="https://cocoaaa.github.io/articles/2020/01/17/paper-data-analysis-with-latent-variable-models" rel="alternate"></link><published>2020-01-17T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2020-01-17T00:00:00-08:00</updated><author><name>Hayley Song</name></author><id>tag:cocoaaa.github.io,2020-01-17:articles/2020/01/17/paper-data-analysis-with-latent-variable-models</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;This is my reading notes for David Blei's Data Analysis with Latent Variable Models, published in Annual Stat Review in 2014: &lt;a href="https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/pdf/10.1146/annurev-statistics-022513-115657"&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry></feed>